                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks [~kou]and [~wesm], I agree to build pyarrow wheels using manylinux1 for generic linux distributions, but how about distribute libarrow-dev with `-D_GLIBCXX_USE_CXX11_ABI=0`?\r\n\r\nCurrent manylinux1 wheels works well if our python pip also built using manylinux1, i.e., gcc-4.8 and without the DUAL abi. But it users install pyarrow wheels and build our package from scratch, things would be broken. ",
